Prime Minister Abe and President Trump had an in-depth discussion over lunch regarding various challenges in the international community, including the issue of North Korea. They expressed their desire to continue discussing global affairs, economic issues, and bilateral matters. President Trump mentioned that they also lightly touched on trade and other subjects, expressing confidence in making progress in reducing trade deficits and promoting fair and equal trade. Both leaders expressed gratitude for the good meeting and the friendships that have been built.